CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 20, 1952, pg. 1 reads: "East Liberty Merchants Paint Windows For Xmas - Businessmen of the 5800 block on Penn Avenue sponsored a competition among the art students of five high schools as they sought to brighten their display windows for the Yule season. Here are the winners... Below is the third prize painting, several traditional scenes by Peabody sophomore Herbert Poindexter (insert) -Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Herbert Poindexter wearing fine patterned houndstooth shirt, posed in storeroom, possibly Harry Garvin's bar & restaurant supply
